Run a package executable

Usage: rx [OPTIONS] [ARGS]...

Arguments:
  [ARGS]...  Rscript options, package ref or command, and tool arguments

Options:
      --from <PKG_REF>     Resolve a package ref and run <command> from that package
  -w, --with <PKG>         Add a dependency for this tool run; may be repeated
      --r-version <SPEC>   Select the R version for this tool run with rig
      --rscript <RSCRIPT>  Select the Rscript executable
  -h, --help               Print help
  -V, --version            Print version

Mental model:
  rx is the package-executable frontend for `ir tool run`.
  It resolves the provider package plus any --with dependencies into an
  isolated cached R library, then launches the selected executable.
  Package executables are discovered from installed package exec/, bin/,
  and architecture-specific bin/<arch>/ directories. bin/ entries are run
  as-is.
  The tool sees the resolved package library plus base, site, and system
  libraries; ambient user R libraries are not used.

Examples:
  rx btw --help
      # shorthand for: rx --from btw btw --help.

  rx --from pkg command --help
      # resolve package `pkg`, run executable `command`.

  rx --from pkg --with cli command --flag value
      # --from and --with are for rx; --flag value is passed to command.

Workflow:
  Use rx for ad hoc package tools and executable frontends.
  Use `ir tool install` for repeated shell use.
  For durable scripts and documents, use `ir run` or `ir render` with
  frontmatter; see `ir quickstart`.

Use `ir tool run --help` for full command details.
